# Normalize all text files to LF in the repository and on checkout, on every
# platform. Without this, Windows runners check out with CRLF (git autocrlf) and
# `prettier --check` — which expects LF — fails the whole repo in CI even though
# nothing is actually wrong. Enforcing LF keeps the green gate identical on
# Windows, Linux, and macOS.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets must never be line-ending normalized.
*.webp binary
*.webm binary
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.ico  binary
*.icns binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
